section.section:
The County Commissioners may not sell or lease the riparian rights adjacent to any real or leasehold property that belongs to Dorchester County and is located in the City of Cambridge unless the County Commissioners provide for the public sale or lease under a process that includes the following elements:
A public advertisement, in at least one newspaper of general circulation in the county, soliciting sealed bids or proposals;
The public opening of sealed bids or proposals;
The rejection of unresponsive or unacceptable bids or proposals; and
The selection of the bidder or offeror who offers the terms most favorable to the county.
